                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/736: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-22T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 22, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For the Minister: Your June 20, 3 p.m., from Shanghai, paragraph (3) concerning
                    your plans.<note n="76" xml:id="d803fn76">Telegram not printed; par. 3 contained
                        the Minister’s request for authorization to leave for Peiping on June
                        26.</note>
                </p>
                <p>If C. T. Wang appears satisfied, the Department authorizes you to return to
                    Peiping on June 26, but prior to your departure your comments are desired as
                    requested in Department’s June 16, 5 p.m., to Shanghai, paragraph (5).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
